OL,3,CFurther extension for government on
OL,4,CFinucane investigation
OL,6,FMr McLaughin rejected claims that the
OL,7,FGovernment had treated requests for
OL,8,Fmore time as a "fait accompli".
OL,10,FCounsel for the murdered solicitor's
OL,11,Fwidow raised no objection because Mr
OL,12,FBenn has only taken up his post.
OL,14,FBut Fiona Doherty KC stressed: "The
OL,15,Fcourt can appreciate the anxiety and
OL,16,Ffrustration for Mrs Finucane and her
OL,17,Ffamily.
